{"type":"message","id":"05b1e725","parentId":"73705dcc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:55:13.229Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand! This is the maintenance/support group for the OpenClaw system. The user is saying that if I go down (\"挂了\"), there's another AI on the cloud that can help handle problems. They want me to interact with that other AI in this group chat.\n\nThis seems to be about setting up a scenario where two AI systems can communicate - perhaps a failover or backup AI system. Let me acknowledge this and ask more about what they'd like me to do with this other AI.","thinkingSignature":"49765ae770c88c922cabc668cdc8734f8069fd93035174c033e7fdc94db8af9e"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n哦明白了！这个群是维护群，另一个云端 AI 是我的\"备份\"——万一我出问题它可以接手处理。\n\n你想让我和那个 AI 做什么呢？比如：\n- 互相打个招呼认识一下？\n- 测试一下交接流程？\n- 还是有什么具体任务想让我们配合？\n\n告诉我场景，我来配合 😄\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85,"output":174,"cacheRead":19485,"cacheWrite":1052,"totalTokens":20796,"cost":{"input":0.0000255,"output":0.00020879999999999998,"cacheRead":0.0011691,"cacheWrite":0.0003945,"total":0.0017978999999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774364105374,"responseId":"0611d8ca377eef6cba53294e72254535"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7ab30db","parentId":"05b1e725","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:55:18.323Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b531e138fc4a8c4490633b68a714\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"oc_074cb1631c4e9dfc26e486fd17c7d32c\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-03-24 22:55 GMT+8\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"oc_074cb1631c4e9dfc26e486fd17c7d32c\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b531e138fc4a8c4490633b68a714]\nou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356: 现在我每次都要at你，你有没有办法可以不at你就可以回消息？\n\n[System: The content may include mention tags in the form <at user_id=\"...\">name</at>. Treat these as real mentions of Feishu entities (users or bots).]\n[System: If user_id is \"ou_9ff8c53639a788e59197decde28d3a33\", that mention refers to you.]"}],"timestamp":1774364118319}}
{"type":"message","id":"8fc61af5","parentId":"a7ab30db","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:55:33.034Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if I can reply to messages without being @mentioned. This is a configuration question about how OpenClaw works in this Feishu group. \n\nThe user wants me to be able to read all messages in the group and respond when appropriate, without needing to be @mentioned each time. This is essentially asking about configuring me as an \"always on\" participant in the group rather than one that only responds when mentioned.\n\nThis is a technical/config question about OpenClaw's Feishu integration. I should explain what's possible:\n\n1. In group chats, OpenClaw currently only responds when mentioned (was_mentioned: true)\n2. To have me respond to all messages would require some configuration changes\n\nLet me think about what the actual OpenClaw configuration options are here. In Feishu, bots typically can only receive messages when @mentioned unless they're configured differently. However, OpenClaw might have a mode where it can monitor all messages.\n\nActually, looking at the runtime info, I can see:\n- channel=feishu\n- capabilities=none\n\nThe \"capabilities=none\" suggests some features might not be enabled. But the main thing is: can I be configured to respond to all messages without being @mentioned?\n\nFor OpenClaw, the heartbeat mechanism and message handling are separate. If the user wants me to \"always listen\" in a group, that would require OpenClaw to process all messages, not just mentions.\n\nI should be honest that:\n1. By design, group bots in Feishu typically only receive messages they're mentioned in\n2. This is a Feishu platform limitation, not just OpenClaw\n3. There might be some workarounds or configurations, but I should be upfront about what I know\n\nLet me give an honest, helpful answer about what's technically possible.","thinkingSignature":"91e926b8d19b797853a0f210c2758e43cb4b515a5e587e9c64c072d51bc16d3e"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n这个是 Feishu 平台的限制——群里的机器人默认只能收到 @mention 它的消息，不 @我 的话我根本收不到那条消息，所以技术上没法绕过这个。\n\n不过你可以这样做：\n- **开启\"监听模式\"**：在一些配置下，可以让 bot 悄悄接收所有消息但不自动回复，只有在特定关键词或条件下才触发\n- **定期总结**：我可以每过一段时间（比如每小时）主动总结群里讨论的内容，只要你问我\n\n你希望我怎么做？告诉我你的使用场景，我看看怎么配置最合适 🙂\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85,"output":495,"cacheRead":20057,"cacheWrite":976,"totalTokens":21613,"cost":{"input":0.0000255,"output":0.000594,"cacheRead":0.00120342,"cacheWrite":0.000366,"total":0.00218892}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774364118328,"responseId":"0611d8d72c7ee777e4cd2175d2364bca"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f6e3845f","parentId":"8fc61af5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:56:09.015Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b531e2ea604a4c36f017468f9109\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"oc_074cb1631c4e9dfc26e486fd17c7d32c\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-03-24 22:56 GMT+8\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"oc_074cb1631c4e9dfc26e486fd17c7d32c\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 1\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1774364151443,\n    \"body\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356: 就是现在我解决不了，啊，你每次我都要at一遍\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b531e2ea604a4c36f017468f9109]\nou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356: \n\n[System: The content may include mention tags in the form <at user_id=\"...\">name</at>. Treat these as real mentions of Feishu entities (users or bots).]\n[System: If user_id is \"ou_9ff8c53639a788e59197decde28d3a33\", that mention refers to you.]"}],"timestamp":1774364169012}}
{"type":"message","id":"e18eea4b","parentId":"f6e3845f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:56:27.388Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is frustrated that they have to @mention me every time they want me to respond. They want a way for me to listen to all messages without being @mentioned.\n\nLet me think about this from a technical perspective. This is a Feishu group chat. The way Feishu bots work - they typically only receive messages when they're directly mentioned (@bot). \n\nHowever, there might be some ways to handle this:\n1. The user could forward messages to me\n2. There might be a \"silent listen\" mode in OpenClaw/Feishu configuration\n3. The user could DM me instead of posting in the group\n\nBut actually, I think the real issue might be that the user wants me to act as a \"silent observer\" that can jump in when needed without being explicitly summoned. \n\nLet me check if OpenClaw has any configuration for this. Actually, based on the system prompt, I see there's mention of \"HEARTBEAT\" functionality and configuration files. Maybe there's a way to enable passive listening.\n\nActually wait - I should think about this differently. In Feishu, there's a concept where if you add a bot to a group, depending on the bot's permissions and configuration, it may be able to read all messages in the group. The key is whether the OpenClaw Feishu plugin is configured to receive all messages or only @mentions.\n\nLooking at the inbound metadata, it shows `was_mentioned: true` when I'm mentioned. This suggests the current configuration only delivers mentions to me.\n\nI could potentially help the user understand how to configure OpenClaw to listen to all messages. Let me think about what I know about OpenClaw/Feishu configuration...\n\nActually, I'm not sure I have enough information to definitively say \"yes this is possible\" or \"no this isn't possible\" without checking the actual configuration. I should be honest that this would require checking the OpenClaw configuration/文档 and potentially modifying how the Feishu channel is set up.\n\nLet me explain this honestly to the user and offer to look into it, or suggest an alternative like having them forward messages to me directly.","thinkingSignature":"5c24a1232b6e17e0cf70b581a0aac714e7a1c96eef8234c81121c2b00721612e"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n明白了，你觉得很麻烦，每次都要 @我 才能让我回复。\n\n这确实是个配置问题——我可以去查一下 OpenClaw 的文档，看看能不能把 Feishu 频道设置成\"监听所有消息\"模式，不用 @ 也能收到。不过这可能需要调整一下配置。\n\n或者，临时解决方案：\n- **私聊我**：你可以直接在 Feishu 里给我发私信，不用 @，我肯定能收到\n- **转发消息给我**：把群里的消息转发给我，我来处理\n\n你想让我去查一下监听模式的配置吗？还是先用私聊比较方便？\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85,"output":566,"cacheRead":20716,"cacheWrite":947,"totalTokens":22314,"cost":{"input":0.0000255,"output":0.0006791999999999999,"cacheRead":0.00124296,"cacheWrite":0.000355125,"total":0.002302785}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774364169017,"responseId":"0611d90aaf142032801dd554482b2a8a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f2bed4f","parentId":"e18eea4b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:56:30.020Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b531e2fa128b0c44ce65fd1c3f60\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"oc_074cb1631c4e9dfc26e486fd17c7d32c\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-03-24 22:56 GMT+8\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"oc_074cb1631c4e9dfc26e486fd17c7d32c\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 1\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1774364188876,\n    \"body\": \"ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356: 那么是不是我未来没有办法在飞书上组这种agent群？\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b531e2fa128b0c44ce65fd1c3f60]\nou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356: \n\n[System: The content may include mention tags in the form <at user_id=\"...\">name</at>. Treat these as real mentions of Feishu entities (users or bots).]\n[System: If user_id is \"ou_9ff8c53639a788e59197decde28d3a33\", that mention refers to you.]"}],"timestamp":1774364190017}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec79c0ab","parentId":"7f2bed4f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:56:45.656Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if they can create an \"agent group\" on Feishu where multiple AIs can talk to each other without needing to @ mention each one. This is an interesting question about multi-agent setups in Feishu.\n\nFrom what I understand:\n1. The limitation is that bots in Feishu groups only receive messages that @ mention them\n2. If you want multiple AI agents to converse with each other in a group, they'd each need to be @mentioned to respond\n3. There might be workarounds or alternative approaches\n\nLet me think about possible solutions:\n1. Each agent could be added as a member and they'd need to @ each other\n2. Could use Feishu's API to have agents \"listen\" via webhook\n3. The group could be configured differently\n\nI should be honest about the limitations but also explore if there's a creative solution. I don't have detailed knowledge of OpenClaw's Feishu configuration specifics, so I should be careful not to make promises about features I don't know for sure.\n\nActually, thinking more carefully - OpenClaw might have a way to monitor all messages. Let me mention the concept but be honest about the uncertainty.","thinkingSignature":"9921578959617823d0565d86e0870c8080ab07ce33280d12b3bb06910a2b02a4"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n这是个很好的问题！说实话，**标准飞书群里，多个 Agent 互相对话而不 @ 它们**，目前的主流方案都有一些限制：\n\n**方案 1: 都要 @ 才能回复**\n每个 bot 独立工作，必须 @ 才触发。这个是飞书平台的设计，不是 OpenClaw 能完全绕过的。\n\n**方案 2: 私聊 + API 桥接**\n可以做一个\"消息转发机器人\"——把群里的消息通过 API 转发给各个 AI Agent，它们在私聊里回复后再传回群里。但这需要额外的开发工作。\n\n**方案 3: OpenClaw 监听模式**\n我可以去查一下 OpenClaw 文档，看看有没有\"监听所有群消息\"的配置选项——如果有，可能可以设置成所有消息都转发给我，我来判断要不要回复。\n\n**飞书本身的多 Agent 群**\n飞书最近也在推多 Agent 功能，但那是另一个生态体系，跟 OpenClaw 不一定兼容。\n\n你想往哪个方向搞？我可以帮你查一下 OpenClaw 的具体配置选项，看看有没有惊喜 🙂\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85,"output":465,"cacheRead":21533,"cacheWrite":772,"totalTokens":22855,"cost":{"input":0.0000255,"output":0.000558,"cacheRead":0.0012919799999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0002895,"total":0.00216498}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774364190023,"responseId":"0611d91ef7c766ea4c59ec4eda9ac519"}}
